Calculation of estimates of construction facilities in the Russian Federation will take place in a new way
The Federal Antimonopoly Service takes special control of pricing, regulation of the construction industry, as well as problems of connection to the grid.
Under the Federal Antimonopoly Service, an expert council for the development of competition in the construction sector was established.
At his meeting, the head of the control of housing and communal services, construction and natural resources of the Federal Antimonopoly Service Vadim Soloviev said that "today's calculation of the estimate of construction facilities is absolutely incomprehensible."
The regulatory base makes pricing opaque and can lead to an unreasonable price of construction, according to the FAS.
And offer the cost of construction of objects of state property at the stage of designing to determine on the basis of market prices of constructive solutions instead of the current estimate norms and single prices for technological operations.
These proposals are included in the "road map" and are now under consideration in the Ministry of Construction.
"The replacement of the traditional estimate documentation in the construction for calculations of structural elements should lead to less corruption in the industry, - explained "RGB" Vadim Soloviev.
After all, now the estimates calculate every bolt and nut, and it is not always possible to check everything, so sometimes in the documentation unscrupulous construction companies can dig "whole tractors."
In the Minstroe agree with the FAS.
"The first work on the transition to the cost calculation on structural elements is already there: methods for calculating prices for constructive solutions, drawing up estimates on these indicators, - said "RGB" head of the Department of Urban Planning and Architecture of the Ministry of Construction Elena Zhukova.
The road construction sector has been chosen as a pilot.
However, experts believe that the problem is much more serious.
As the head of the construction company "Profi-invest" Anatoly Demianko said, the estimate standards have long been outdated, but another mechanism has not been proposed to the business.
"As for the proposed calculations on structural elements, in practice, it is difficult to implement, as in the construction of buildings are often used completely different technologies," he said.
It is no secret that the construction market develops largely due to the state order.
