Deputy Director for Engineering of the Sectoral Center for Capital Construction Rosatom Vladimir Malakhov drew attention to the fact that today the market is conventionally divided into companies that have access to the portfolio of contracts, and to companies that own monopoly competencies and do not allow competitors to this field.
He believes that the creation of a transparent market is possible only if access to contracts will be maximally protected from someone's management impact.
The expert council proposed to form a system of state order in such a way that the same performer is not entitled to receive more than one contract in the amount of more than 1 billion rubles. or several contracts worth more than 1 billion rubles.
The Ministry of Defense believes that this approach should be assessed in terms of influence on business, as well as the efficiency of construction management.
As explained by Elena Zhukova, in this case it will be necessary to give the customer the functions of the general contractor, which will lead to an increase in the staffing number of the customer and budget expenditures for its maintenance.
At the same time, the specialists of the customer will have to have knowledge to assess the quality of the works performed by contractors, as well as their safety.
Often with such a breakdown it will be necessary to determine who will be responsible for the security of the object as a whole.
In addition, this approach may result in the outflow of highly qualified participants in public procurement due to the lack of interest in obtaining a state order for incomplete work and a small amount of the contract.
Alexander Evstashenkov, deputy head of the Expert Consulting Center of the Procurement Institute, believes that now the procedure of the state order has become a business game for the attention of the contractor.
And he cited the following example: "the participant when filling in the application must indicate "specific indicators" without the indication of the words: "or equivalent," "should be," "from," "better," "less," "neagrogue," "similar," "similar to," "not lower," "be higher," "may," "may," "may," "be," "be," "previously," "not earlier," "not above."
Thus, customers often abuse their right to establish requirements for the content of the application submitted by contractors.
Another problem of the 44-FZ, according to Yevstashenkov, was the need to assess at the stage of filing the quality of work through the "paper" proposal of the participant.
Considering the application of the participant, you can really assess only the qualification of the contractor, but not the quality of the work, which have not even started, - the expert believes.
The quality of the work can be evaluated only when they receive.
The expert council also proposed to transfer marginal income from the upper to the lower echelon to the lower echelon to the intermediate contractors.
Chairman of the Expert Council, State Secretary, deputy head of the Federal Antimonopoly Service Andrei Tsarikovsky believes that this should not be done, as the general contractor should be responsible for the order.
Otherwise, it will turn out, as in the well-known reprise of Arkady Raikin "Atele": "There are claims to buttons?"
