"Europrotocol" instead of reference traffic police
Payments on the helmet can be received without a certificate of traffic police - so the Central Bank intends to stimulate the introduction of "Europrotocol" in Russia.
The Bank of Russia has developed a draft instructions, according to which from September 1 this year to receive payments on the helmet insured motorist will be able to do without a certificate of traffic police.
It is, however, only about the cases when the accident was issued by "Europrotocol" without the participation of road police.
That is, if the accident involved only two cars, there are no physically affected persons, the damage does not exceed the established limit and both drivers have reached agreement in the question of who is the culprit of the accident.
From August 2, the payout limit on the "Europrotocol" is 50 thousand. rubles, and from October 1 in Moscow, St. Petersburg, as well as in the Moscow and Leningrad regions it will be increased to 400 thousand. rub.
The point is that often even with minor damage, in a situation where an accident can be issued by "Europrotocol," drivers caught in the accident, cause the PCT.
After all, if there is a policy casco to get on it compensation without a certificate of traffic police was impossible.
The parameters prescribed in the draft instructions are just designed to eliminate this obstacle in the way of introduction of the "Europrotocol" in Russia.
According to them, the maximum cash payment in connection with an accident, issued without traffic police staff, should not be lower than the limit on the "Europrotocol."
But at the same time it can not be above the limit defined in the contract of insurance casco.
The idea is certainly useful and theoretically able to unload both employees of the PCT and roads.
But, most likely, neither motorists nor insurers will be delighted from it.
The latter are already talking about a serious threat to the growth of fraud, which can lead to the introduction of new rules of payments on the helmet.
As for drivers, it is difficult to imagine what kind of work will have to be done to overcome the native Russian conservatism.
